WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.470 --> 00:00:05.230
Inarizaki                                                           Karasuno

2
00:00:10.190 --> 00:00:11.860
We Don't Need the Memories

3
00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:16.760
Nishinoya!

4
00:00:21.410 --> 00:00:23.460
All right!

5
00:00:24.370 --> 00:00:25.710
I knew it...

6
00:00:25.710 --> 00:00:26.630
Yeah...

7
00:00:27.440 --> 00:00:28.980
Miya Atsumu

8
00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:32.590
has been targeting Nishinoya 
ever since the second set.

9
00:00:33.270 --> 00:00:37.900
It looks like all the servers are 
deliberately trying to avoid Nishinoya.

10
00:00:38.890 --> 00:00:41.770
This is probably Nishinoya's first time...

11
00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:44.900
He's going through the 
humiliation of being targeted.

12
00:00:59.030 --> 00:01:06.040
Haikyu!!

13
00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:18.950
Miyagi
Karasuno

14
00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:22.030
Episode 19: The Ultimate Challengers

15
00:02:18.330 --> 00:02:18.950
Chikara.

16
00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:22.910
Could you tape me up? I suck at it.

17
00:02:22.910 --> 00:02:23.700
Sure.

18
00:02:24.290 --> 00:02:26.410
Did you sprain your finger? Are you okay?

19
00:02:26.410 --> 00:02:28.300
Yeah, I'm fine.

20
00:02:29.810 --> 00:02:33.100
Inarizaki #7's serve is intense.

21
00:02:33.100 --> 00:02:37.310
Yeah. And he's going after the libero,
 who can only defend.

22
00:02:37.310 --> 00:02:38.280
Oh?

23
00:02:38.280 --> 00:02:40.780
That libero's really good 
and full of energy.

24
00:02:40.780 --> 00:02:43.400
If they crush him, that team's in trouble.

25
00:02:43.400 --> 00:02:44.350
Really?

26
00:02:44.750 --> 00:02:49.020
"There's no way we can pick up balls 
that even our libero can't get..."

27
00:02:50.250 --> 00:02:56.010
That's probably what Miya Atsumu is thinking,
 so he's putting pressure on them that way.

28
00:02:56.680 --> 00:03:01.280
It always feels great when you get a 
service ace against a strong opponent.

29
00:03:03.240 --> 00:03:04.430
There he goes.

30
00:03:05.080 --> 00:03:05.660
What?

31
00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:10.300
Atsumu is amazingly, 
incredibly thoughtless at times.

32
00:03:10.300 --> 00:03:12.250
Huh?! That's so rude!

33
00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:14.960
All right!

34
00:03:16.600 --> 00:03:18.920
You've got this, Nishinoya-san...

35
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:32.760
Nice serve!

36
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:33.270
We Don't Need the Memories

37
00:03:33.270 --> 00:03:37.520
Inarizaki High School

38
00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:40.500
Four steps...

39
00:03:41.250 --> 00:03:42.630
So it's going to be a jump floater.

40
00:03:58.580 --> 00:04:00.060
Miya Atsumu...

41
00:04:00.060 --> 00:04:03.530
manages to get two service 
aces against their libero!

42
00:04:00.750 --> 00:04:04.760
Nice serve, Atsumu! Nice serve, 
Atsumu! Push it, push it, Atsumu!

43
00:04:04.760 --> 00:04:07.220
One more time!

44
00:04:14.610 --> 00:04:17.320
It totally looked like he got that.

45
00:04:17.320 --> 00:04:19.900
Its path seemed to change 
right by his hands.

46
00:04:20.790 --> 00:04:23.800
When you're digging the ball, the surface 
that the ball can hit is narrow.

47
00:04:23.800 --> 00:04:27.720
If the point where it hits is just a 
bit off, the ball goes a weird way.

48
00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:28.820
Yeah, totally!

49
00:04:29.860 --> 00:04:33.120
Nishinoya missing two serve 
receives in a row is just...

50
00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:34.580
I've never seen him do that.

51
00:04:36.210 --> 00:04:40.360
Volleyball isn't a sport where you 
can finish things off on your own.

52
00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:45.500
If you can't get the first receive up,
 nothing's gonna start.

53
00:04:46.460 --> 00:04:51.720
That's why the emotional damage from 
missing a serve receive is huge.

54
00:04:52.710 --> 00:04:56.730
Not to mention, if the libero, 
who's in charge of defense, can't defend,

55
00:04:56.730 --> 00:04:59.290
there's no point in him being on the court.

56
00:05:03.140 --> 00:05:06.780
I can't count how many times 
Nishinoya's cheered me up.

57
00:05:07.320 --> 00:05:10.330
Because you have me guarding your backs.

58
00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:15.470
What am I supposed to say to him?

59
00:05:15.470 --> 00:05:17.070
Noya-san—Whoa!

60
00:05:20.580 --> 00:05:21.710
The hell?

61
00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:21.710
What's he doing?

62
00:05:23.330 --> 00:05:26.760
The penalty finger push-ups from practice...

63
00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:30.920
Nishinoya's doing his best 
to stay calm right now.

64
00:05:41.730 --> 00:05:43.900
That guy's the best.

65
00:05:56.910 --> 00:05:57.960
Yes!

66
00:05:57.960 --> 00:05:58.870
Follow up!

67
00:05:59.640 --> 00:06:00.580
Cover!

68
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:02.880
That was a weak receive!

69
00:06:03.960 --> 00:06:05.690
Asahi-san!

70
00:06:08.330 --> 00:06:10.010
I'm not gonna be able to 
hit it that hard.

71
00:06:13.570 --> 00:06:14.640
He went for the setter!

72
00:06:14.640 --> 00:06:16.600
The first to touch the ball is Miya Atsumu!

73
00:06:16.600 --> 00:06:19.660
At the same time, Miya Osamu
 is right under the ball!

74
00:06:22.600 --> 00:06:26.240
He's not even a setter and he pulled 
off a C-pass?! On a counter, too!

75
00:06:27.280 --> 00:06:29.020
He's covering for his twin.

76
00:06:30.570 --> 00:06:31.820
That's within expectations.

77
00:06:36.120 --> 00:06:37.200
Got him.

78
00:06:44.040 --> 00:06:47.010
We Don't Need the Memories

79
00:06:44.600 --> 00:06:48.970
The one who just got the ball up wasn't 
the setter. It was Miya Osamu!

80
00:06:47.520 --> 00:06:48.160
Nice kill.

81
00:06:48.160 --> 00:06:48.970
Nice toss.

82
00:06:49.480 --> 00:06:51.450
What was that just now?

83
00:06:52.250 --> 00:06:54.470
He totally had that block.

84
00:06:54.870 --> 00:06:56.390
Don't worry.

85
00:06:56.850 --> 00:06:59.500
You're a great blocker.

86
00:07:03.380 --> 00:07:04.840
Jackass.

87
00:07:06.110 --> 00:07:09.360
Inarizaki                                                                                 Karasuno

88
00:07:07.760 --> 00:07:09.360
They got another one.

89
00:07:10.050 --> 00:07:14.060
What's up with Suna-kun? He wasn't 
standing out much on offense at first,

90
00:07:14.060 --> 00:07:15.630
but is he getting into his groove?

91
00:07:15.630 --> 00:07:18.340
Rintaro starts off slow.

92
00:07:19.160 --> 00:07:20.870
And I'll have you know...

93
00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:24.140
He knows how to control 
the opposing team's blockers.

94
00:07:25.990 --> 00:07:29.910
Rintaro's weapon is his wide 
contact point from side to side.

95
00:07:30.440 --> 00:07:34.270
If a normal guy's range is about this much,

96
00:07:34.270 --> 00:07:35.700
Rintaro's range is about this much.

97
00:07:36.210 --> 00:07:40.740
When he spikes, he doesn't just 
use his arm or his shoulder.

98
00:07:40.740 --> 00:07:42.250
He uses his whole upper body.

99
00:07:42.250 --> 00:07:43.930
His core.

100
00:07:44.660 --> 00:07:48.440
Since he uses his whole upper body,
 his spikes stay powerful.

101
00:07:48.440 --> 00:07:52.390
It's completely different from 
just lightly tapping on the ball.

102
00:07:53.720 --> 00:07:58.140
I don't really get it... But basically, 
when he's about to get blocked,

103
00:07:58.140 --> 00:08:01.620
he somehow gets through the block. 
It's happened a few times.

104
00:08:03.880 --> 00:08:06.880
Oh, and what about him 
controlling the blockers?

105
00:08:07.850 --> 00:08:09.220
Just watch.

106
00:08:24.280 --> 00:08:25.600
Out!

107
00:08:28.670 --> 00:08:29.670
Damn it!

108
00:08:30.670 --> 00:08:34.060
All right! Asahi, get a nice serve in!

109
00:08:31.360 --> 00:08:34.060
Why are you all sad that I messed up?

110
00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:36.880
Fire it up, fire it up, Karasuno!

111
00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:37.700
Inarizaki                                                                                 Karasuno

112
00:08:36.880 --> 00:08:38.810
Get it, get it, Karasuno!

113
00:08:38.810 --> 00:08:40.810
Fire it up, fire it up, Karasuno!

114
00:08:40.810 --> 00:08:43.060
Get it, get it, Karasuno!

115
00:08:45.370 --> 00:08:46.310
Aran!

116
00:08:50.800 --> 00:08:51.660
Yes!

117
00:08:51.660 --> 00:08:54.220
That was a powerful service ace!

118
00:08:52.680 --> 00:08:53.440
Sorry.

119
00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:54.220
Worry about next time.

120
00:08:54.540 --> 00:08:57.420
Karasuno hasn't been doing their best 
with serves in the second set,

121
00:08:57.420 --> 00:08:59.770
so hopefully they can 
turn things around here.

122
00:09:03.050 --> 00:09:04.100
Aran!

123
00:09:15.360 --> 00:09:17.820
Go! Block that ball, Tsukki!

124
00:09:20.880 --> 00:09:21.990
Two blockers!

125
00:09:23.350 --> 00:09:24.540
Well done.

126
00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:37.050
We Don't Need the Memories

127
00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:39.080
Nice kill, Rintaro! Yes, yes, 
Rintaro! One more time!

128
00:09:41.460 --> 00:09:43.970
The better the blockers are,

129
00:09:44.850 --> 00:09:48.520
the easier it is for Suna 
to control them.

130
00:09:49.980 --> 00:09:56.990
Haikyu!!

131
00:09:56.990 --> 00:10:03.990
Haikyu!!

132
00:10:14.680 --> 00:10:16.860
Well, did you see that?

133
00:10:16.860 --> 00:10:17.970
Huh? Wha?

134
00:10:17.970 --> 00:10:19.470
Inarizaki                                              Karasuno

135
00:10:22.070 --> 00:10:23.210
Did you figure it out?

136
00:10:24.960 --> 00:10:28.020
Their #10 looked totally ready 
 to hit a cross shot.

137
00:10:28.720 --> 00:10:32.440
Tsukki immediately reacted to 
that and tried to block him off,

138
00:10:32.440 --> 00:10:34.900
and Kageyama also immediately 
jumped in to support him.

139
00:10:35.490 --> 00:10:36.360
But...

140
00:10:37.010 --> 00:10:39.320
His approach and the way his 
body's facing are both feints.

141
00:10:39.320 --> 00:10:41.530
He lures the blockers into thinking 
he's going to do a cross shot,

142
00:10:41.530 --> 00:10:43.740
then does the opposite midair.

143
00:10:44.200 --> 00:10:48.210
And he does all this without 
losing any power to his spikes.

144
00:10:48.800 --> 00:10:53.500
Middle blockers' quicks usually end 
up more compact than other attacks.

145
00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:56.800
They're usually quick enough 
to get through the blockers.

146
00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:57.920
But...

147
00:10:57.920 --> 00:11:01.440
Rintaro can use his quick to go head to head

148
00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:04.350
against the blockers once the toss goes up.

149
00:11:04.350 --> 00:11:06.170
Man,

150
00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:09.360
nationals are scary.

151
00:11:10.530 --> 00:11:14.300
We just need to get them off their 
game so they can't use their quicks!

152
00:11:14.300 --> 00:11:16.380
We need to go all out with our 
serves and spikes!

153
00:11:16.380 --> 00:11:17.570
Yeah!

154
00:11:22.490 --> 00:11:23.540
Nishinoya!

155
00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:25.530
Nice receive!

156
00:11:25.530 --> 00:11:27.160
Another powerful serve!

157
00:11:27.160 --> 00:11:29.120
The fact that he managed to 
get it up is amazing, too.

158
00:11:30.520 --> 00:11:32.220
One touch! Cover!

159
00:11:33.490 --> 00:11:34.490
Left!

160
00:11:35.700 --> 00:11:37.100
Three blockers!

161
00:11:39.920 --> 00:11:42.130
That was an intense spike from Ojiro Aran!

162
00:11:42.130 --> 00:11:43.430
The ball is right above the net!

163
00:11:45.180 --> 00:11:46.470
Akagi!

164
00:11:45.180 --> 00:11:46.470
Kageyama pushes it in!

165
00:11:46.950 --> 00:11:47.970
Left!

166
00:11:48.700 --> 00:11:50.700
Here comes Ojiro Aran from the left again!

167
00:11:50.700 --> 00:11:52.140
Stop him!

168
00:11:52.140 --> 00:11:53.650
No slacking!

169
00:11:55.140 --> 00:11:56.550
Three blockers!

170
00:12:03.050 --> 00:12:05.990
That spike got past the three 
blockers and packed a punch!

171
00:12:05.990 --> 00:12:08.490
It might've gone above the block.
 That was high!

172
00:12:08.490 --> 00:12:11.250
But now, Karasuno has a chance 
to fight back, and—

173
00:12:16.040 --> 00:12:17.670
Yeah!

174
00:12:17.670 --> 00:12:20.120
Ojiro Aran slams it into their court!

175
00:12:20.120 --> 00:12:24.680
He managed to get three spikes over
 in a less-than-ideal situation.

176
00:12:24.680 --> 00:12:27.180
He truly tore through for that point!

177
00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:31.850
Inarizaki                                                                      Karasuno

178
00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:34.040
Nice kill, Aran! Jump, 
jump, Aran! One more time!

179
00:12:34.040 --> 00:12:35.770
Not yet, Sensei.

180
00:12:35.770 --> 00:12:39.360
That was clearly our mistake. 
Our boys know that.

181
00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:44.070
More importantly, we don't want to let Ojiro 
Aran rest for even 30 seconds right now.

182
00:12:44.070 --> 00:12:47.590
Yeesh. Their #4 reminds me of Ushiwaka.

183
00:12:48.040 --> 00:12:51.750
What makes him different from Ushiwaka 
is that he's actually receiving serves.

184
00:12:52.800 --> 00:12:55.000
Meaning they can aim their serves at him,

185
00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:59.000
and they've actually gotten quite 
a few service aces against him.

186
00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:01.530
That's definitely a stressor.

187
00:13:02.790 --> 00:13:06.490
And there are plenty of 
difficult tosses going up,

188
00:13:06.490 --> 00:13:08.710
followed by a bunch of solid blocks.

189
00:13:09.300 --> 00:13:12.520
His exhaustion and irritation are 
definitely brewing, as they should be.

190
00:13:13.060 --> 00:13:14.140
Or so I think!

191
00:13:19.480 --> 00:13:20.950
Sorry, follow!

192
00:13:21.440 --> 00:13:22.650
Tanaka-san!

193
00:13:25.970 --> 00:13:27.530
Yeah!

194
00:13:27.530 --> 00:13:29.530
Ryu, you're so badass!

195
00:13:27.530 --> 00:13:30.990
Fly

196
00:13:29.530 --> 00:13:32.190
Tanaka Ryunosuke from Karasuno High School!

197
00:13:31.280 --> 00:13:33.040
Good job, Tanaka!

198
00:13:32.190 --> 00:13:34.960
He's breaking through Inarizaki's 
obvious advantage with that one.

199
00:13:33.040 --> 00:13:34.380
Tanaka-san, nice kill!

200
00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:35.750
Yes!

201
00:13:36.530 --> 00:13:40.420
And now, Karasuno High School is going 
to bring in the third-year Sugawara.

202
00:13:40.930 --> 00:13:43.150
I'll get revenge for Nishinoya.

203
00:13:43.150 --> 00:13:44.880
I'm not dead!

204
00:13:45.570 --> 00:13:48.650
Sugawara-san's going in 
to replace Tsukishima.

205
00:13:48.650 --> 00:13:52.570
Which probably means that 
Kinoshita won't be serving.

206
00:14:00.520 --> 00:14:03.230
That was my 25th service 
ace in my visual training.

207
00:14:05.750 --> 00:14:07.200
Hey!

208
00:14:07.630 --> 00:14:09.200
We took the first set,

209
00:14:09.200 --> 00:14:12.660
but you guys aren't actually thinking that we
can let them have the second set, are you?

210
00:14:13.240 --> 00:14:15.930
We're winning this thing at 2-0!

211
00:14:15.930 --> 00:14:18.370
Yeah!

212
00:14:23.960 --> 00:14:28.800
Jaybird Inn

213
00:14:25.330 --> 00:14:28.800
I want you to put pressure on 
Ojiro Aran as much as possible.

214
00:14:29.240 --> 00:14:31.440
With blocks, and of course, serves.

215
00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:34.500
I definitely won't complain if 
you get service aces off of him,

216
00:14:35.990 --> 00:14:38.970
but the ideal is to get 
him to fall to one knee.

217
00:14:39.760 --> 00:14:43.480
Even if I'm only on the 
court for twenty, ten...

218
00:14:44.500 --> 00:14:46.230
Even five seconds...

219
00:14:46.550 --> 00:14:48.760
I'm going to annoy the hell out of Inarizaki!

220
00:14:49.720 --> 00:14:51.160
Front! Front!

221
00:14:51.580 --> 00:14:54.570
That was a rather risky shot
 for Karasuno's Sugawara!

222
00:14:55.490 --> 00:14:56.710
Osamu!

223
00:15:05.270 --> 00:15:06.680
Kageyama, get the last!

224
00:15:09.380 --> 00:15:10.650
Left!

225
00:15:10.650 --> 00:15:11.890
Yeah, yeah.

226
00:15:13.890 --> 00:15:15.390
It's a bit low...

227
00:15:26.360 --> 00:15:31.590
Nice kill, Aran! Nice kill, Aran! 
Jump, jump, Aran! One more time!

228
00:15:28.790 --> 00:15:30.910
Aran, calm down!

229
00:15:30.910 --> 00:15:31.740
Right!

230
00:15:33.910 --> 00:15:36.240
This time Inarizaki is 
using their pinch server.

231
00:15:36.600 --> 00:15:39.210
The first-year, Riseki Heisuke.

232
00:15:39.990 --> 00:15:43.080
I spent all three years of 
middle school on the bench.

233
00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:47.210
The one time I came on as a pinch server, 
I messed up my serve and that was it.

234
00:15:47.210 --> 00:15:49.500
Nice serve!

235
00:15:47.210 --> 00:15:50.170
We Don't Need the Memories

236
00:15:51.090 --> 00:15:53.730
There's no point if I miss.

237
00:15:53.730 --> 00:15:55.390
I need to get that point.

238
00:15:56.360 --> 00:15:57.590
I'm getting it in there.

239
00:15:58.800 --> 00:16:01.320
Well, Riseki definitely got 
the ball into the court.

240
00:16:02.590 --> 00:16:03.200
Asahi!

241
00:16:03.200 --> 00:16:04.040
Got it!

242
00:16:09.940 --> 00:16:11.900
Heck yeah!

243
00:16:12.150 --> 00:16:14.860
We Don't Need the Memories

244
00:16:17.360 --> 00:16:19.020
What the hell was that serve?!

245
00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:20.160
Why are you even here?!

246
00:16:20.160 --> 00:16:21.930
No one asked you to just give them the ball!

247
00:16:21.930 --> 00:16:24.000
Wow, I haven't heard this in a while.

248
00:16:24.520 --> 00:16:25.630
What is this?

249
00:16:25.630 --> 00:16:27.880
Booing? They're booing their own side?

250
00:16:27.880 --> 00:16:29.850
But he didn't miss the serve, did he?

251
00:16:29.850 --> 00:16:31.330
What is this?

252
00:16:31.330 --> 00:16:34.150
Inarizaki's harsh critiques.

253
00:16:34.150 --> 00:16:39.760
I heard that if you make a weak play, 
their cheer squad gives you an earful.

254
00:16:39.760 --> 00:16:41.710
You're probably hearing it now.

255
00:16:41.710 --> 00:16:44.730
Aw, that's really mean, 
considering he's not even a pro.

256
00:16:47.940 --> 00:16:51.160
This is why I told you to take that chance.

257
00:16:51.160 --> 00:16:53.640
You always think too hard about this.

258
00:16:54.280 --> 00:16:57.510
We don't need a guy who just 
gets the serve over on our team.

259
00:17:00.230 --> 00:17:03.080
Whether we're in the lead or not.

260
00:17:05.480 --> 00:17:06.550
Right.

261
00:17:10.460 --> 00:17:14.220
Fly

262
00:17:35.200 --> 00:17:37.740
A no-touch ace!

263
00:17:37.740 --> 00:17:40.430
That speed! That direction!

264
00:17:38.900 --> 00:17:39.950
Sorry!

265
00:17:39.950 --> 00:17:41.120
Get over it! Don't worry about it!

266
00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:44.080
No one was gonna be able to touch that one.

267
00:17:44.080 --> 00:17:45.080
That's...

268
00:17:45.340 --> 00:17:46.990
Kalm Kageyama.

269
00:17:46.990 --> 00:17:48.990
The hell are you talking about?

270
00:17:48.990 --> 00:17:51.800
I think it's pretty self-explanatory, 
but it's a calm Kageyama.

271
00:17:54.840 --> 00:17:57.770
Like when I'm able to do quicks 
without closing my eyes,

272
00:18:00.120 --> 00:18:03.770
or when he got Tsukishima's point 
of impact higher. Times like that.

273
00:18:05.360 --> 00:18:08.440
It's basically when he's 
in the most tip-top shape.

274
00:18:08.930 --> 00:18:11.770
But it's only his face that's calm.

275
00:18:11.770 --> 00:18:14.780
He's still as harsh as ever, 
so you need to proceed with caution.

276
00:18:14.780 --> 00:18:17.910
This tends to happen a lot 
when facing a powerful foe.

277
00:18:18.400 --> 00:18:20.660
At some point, you turned 
into an instruction manual.

278
00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:26.600
The air is really prickly.

279
00:18:28.480 --> 00:18:30.830
Inarizaki High is calling 
their first timeout.

280
00:18:30.830 --> 00:18:33.070
Let's go, Ina High!

281
00:18:30.830 --> 00:18:33.800
We Don't Need the Memories

282
00:18:31.760 --> 00:18:34.430
But wow, both sides have 
some really powerful serves.

283
00:18:33.800 --> 00:18:37.510
Fly

284
00:18:34.430 --> 00:18:37.510
Both schools have a variety of 
attacks that are very powerful.

285
00:18:37.870 --> 00:18:41.720
If they don't get aggressive with their 
serves and stop the other team's quicks,

286
00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:41.720
Just keep pressing the attack like you 
have been. Don't falter on receiving, either.

287
00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:43.990
the other side will definitely get a point.

288
00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:45.020
I'm sure you're all tired 
about now, but so are they.

289
00:18:45.020 --> 00:18:46.680
We've got the game in our court right now.

290
00:18:46.990 --> 00:18:51.100
Will Kageyama's serves turn the 
tables around for Karasuno?

291
00:18:49.320 --> 00:18:51.100
Make sure you concentrate.

292
00:18:51.100 --> 00:18:52.100
Right!

293
00:19:05.320 --> 00:19:05.950
Yes!

294
00:19:06.560 --> 00:19:08.160
He got another one in!

295
00:19:06.820 --> 00:19:08.160
All right!

296
00:19:08.430 --> 00:19:12.080
That timeout sure didn't 
kill his concentration!

297
00:19:10.120 --> 00:19:12.080
Miya Osamu                            Miya Atsumu

298
00:19:10.400 --> 00:19:12.080
Seriously?

299
00:19:17.670 --> 00:19:19.670
One more time!

300
00:19:20.880 --> 00:19:21.700
Gin!

301
00:19:22.840 --> 00:19:23.820
Aran!

302
00:19:25.360 --> 00:19:27.990
Even if we can't totally 
break them down mentally,

303
00:19:28.770 --> 00:19:30.730
just the slightest annoyance...

304
00:19:31.480 --> 00:19:34.900
If they hit aggressive spikes
 toward us even a little...

305
00:19:34.900 --> 00:19:35.930
Left, left!

306
00:19:35.930 --> 00:19:37.400
Three blockers!

307
00:19:50.870 --> 00:19:53.770
That'll give us a huge 
chance for a turnaround.

308
00:19:54.960 --> 00:19:56.640
Yes, yes, yes, yes!

309
00:19:56.640 --> 00:19:57.840
Here it comes!

310
00:19:58.310 --> 00:20:00.060
Oh, hey. Is that...

311
00:20:00.060 --> 00:20:01.050
Yeah...

312
00:20:02.360 --> 00:20:04.460
That was an annoying out.

313
00:20:05.510 --> 00:20:07.470
Fire it up, fire it up, Karasuno!

314
00:20:05.510 --> 00:20:07.470
Fly

315
00:20:12.640 --> 00:20:13.260
Damn it!

316
00:20:13.260 --> 00:20:15.360
And the ball is sailing right 
back over to Karasuno's side.

317
00:20:21.030 --> 00:20:22.450
Too damn fast!

318
00:20:24.880 --> 00:20:27.160
Don't go getting a big head, now.

319
00:20:28.870 --> 00:20:29.940
Samu!

320
00:20:32.920 --> 00:20:34.040
Yeah!

321
00:20:34.040 --> 00:20:36.970
Ojiro Aran definitely got that one over.

322
00:20:35.550 --> 00:20:38.960
Nice, nice, Aran! One more time!

323
00:20:36.970 --> 00:20:38.960
He's making his presence known as the ace!

324
00:20:39.430 --> 00:20:42.460
Atsumu-kun's dig was amazing.

325
00:20:43.420 --> 00:20:47.480
But Kageyama Tobio and Miya Atsumu are 
candidates for the national youth team

326
00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:49.440
and excellent setters.

327
00:20:49.440 --> 00:20:52.120
You can see the sparks fly 
even when they're not setting.

328
00:20:53.270 --> 00:20:56.220
Osamu! Put the finisher on 
this second set already!

329
00:20:56.220 --> 00:20:59.630
Also, I definitely got way more 
service aces than you today!

330
00:20:59.630 --> 00:21:00.820
Would you shut up?

331
00:21:06.120 --> 00:21:07.200
Shit.

332
00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:12.120
Inarizaki

333
00:21:12.120 --> 00:21:15.850
That was a little too powerful 
and definitely went out.

334
00:21:16.930 --> 00:21:18.080
It took flight!

335
00:21:18.430 --> 00:21:20.880
You don't need to hit a home run here!

336
00:21:20.880 --> 00:21:22.900
You do that too, sometimes!

337
00:21:23.240 --> 00:21:25.100
It's because you provoked him.

338
00:21:25.100 --> 00:21:26.050
Ow!

339
00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:30.300
Osamu-kun looks pretty calm, but hates losing.

340
00:21:30.300 --> 00:21:33.270
Well, think about who his other half is.

341
00:21:36.140 --> 00:21:38.980
Even the slightest wavering 
of their mental strength...

342
00:21:38.980 --> 00:21:42.730
will throw them off their 
usual plays just a bit...

343
00:21:42.730 --> 00:21:43.950
It's in!

344
00:21:42.730 --> 00:21:46.060
Then irregularities start to pile up.

345
00:21:43.950 --> 00:21:44.990
Gin!

346
00:21:56.610 --> 00:21:58.780
And that changes the flow.

347
00:22:04.710 --> 00:22:05.440
Sorry!

348
00:22:05.440 --> 00:22:06.110
Don't worry about it!

349
00:22:06.110 --> 00:22:07.660
It's all good, Asahi-san.

350
00:22:07.660 --> 00:22:08.220
Sorry!

351
00:22:08.220 --> 00:22:11.140
Let's get our rhythm back. Let's calm down.

352
00:23:51.950 --> 00:23:56.950
Episode 20: Leader

353
00:23:53.460 --> 00:23:55.660
Next time, "Leader."
